The paper proposes a new regularization method for deep learning models to improve their generalization performance. The method involves modifying the input variables using a linear transformation based on their contribution to the final prediction. This falls under the category of regularization techniques in machine learning, which is a subfield of both computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the proposed method on classification tasks, which is a common application of deep learning models and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the robustness of the model to out-of-distribution samples, which is a topic of interest in natural language processing (cs.CL) and neural networks (cs.NE).
